raw_data.title: Strategic Council
raw_data.description: Oversight needed by owners to include any major issues, concerns, meetings and leadership needs.

raw_data.title: Designer
raw_data.description: The designer is responsible for designing creative products based on the creative direction, conceptual design and image branding decisions provided by a collaboration of the client and team. Designer applies creative design to collateral marketing material, print, radio, TV, cable, film, video, website and exhibits.  Typical tasks include: developing conceptual design and layouts; providing basic copywriting and technical writing services; developing publication designs and/or typographic layout; and furnishing custom or stock artwork (including electronic artwork).

raw_data.title: Social Media Specialist
raw_data.description: The Social Media Specialist is quick thinking and has a keen eye for editing and current social media trends. Familiarity in the social media space is required as social media platforms is the center of this position. The following is necessary for this role: Content creation, Manage multiple Feeds , Social calendar development, Social reputation management, Social trend monitoring/analysis, Find/create/resize images to use for social posts, Research hashtags and mentions, Proofread clients content - all links/mentions are correct, Schedule content posts, Weekly updates for clients, Researching and bringing new technologies.

raw_data.title: Web Developer
raw_data.description: The Web developer must have  2+ years Advanced WordPress experience. This multi-talented individual that can manage projects with partners and give creative direction on web builds as well as implement tags, code and identify optimizations for improvement on page. The following is necessary for this role: Monthly website backups, Monthly website plugin and system updates, Website builds, Landing/Funnel page creation, fulfillment & optimization, Domain DNS setup, Online Form Fill creation, Ecommerce system maintenance, CSS styling, Basic SEO implementation, Mobile responsive web layout practices, Project/Team management for website creation by partners, HTML5 Ad Fulfillment, Tag Deployment on Sites.

raw_data.title: Content Writer
raw_data.description: The Content Writer will write and direct copy for advertisements, marketing collateral, proposals and other related business communications and corporate communication packages. Develop highly creative promotion concepts and copy for all elements required to execute consumer marketing and trade promotion programs for clients. Work as team member with the Account Planning, Creative and Account Service Teams to conceptualize and develop strategic marketing programs that will have an impact on the business of the agency’s clients. Provide strategic thinking on all of the agency’s accounts while developing and implementing a marketing/promotion vision that expands both client and agency opportunities for brand building and proofing. Organize assignments and workflow, maintaining the proper channels of communication and areas of responsibility to ensure all timelines.  Actively participate in brainstorms, creative briefings and client presentations, when necessary. Stay abreast of current trends, communication techniques and marketing promotions.  Maintain the integrity of the clients message across all communication elements by providing thought leadership and fully understanding our clients’ products/services. Ensure all program elements consistently and uniformly meet the objectives as set forth by the original creative brief and/or supplemental information.

raw_data.title: Programmer
raw_data.description: A Java, C#, .Net, C, Sybase and Oracle Programmer is responsible for the development, design and implementation of new or modified software products or ongoing business projects. The following is necessary for this role: Researching, designing, implementing and managing software programs, Testing and evaluating new programs, Identifying areas for modification in existing programs and subsequently developing these modifications, Writing and implementing efficient code, Determining operational practicality, Developing quality assurance procedures, Deploying software tools, processes and metrics, Maintaining and upgrading existing systems, Training users.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: The Project Manager guides all involved with a project from start to finish, ensuring timely completion. Serves as the primary point of contact between clients and internal functional groups, including  marketing  strategy,  creative  services,  marketing/communications,  market research information  management  and print/production  management.  Schedules  every  task  of  every  project,  coordinates  functional group  assignments  and  ensures  the  integration  of  client  direction  and  feedback.  Provides status  reports  to the client and  internal  team  on  a  weekly basis  and  facilitates communication  among team members. Assists in the development of marketing strategies and tactical procedures.

raw_data.description: Translate business client needs into video and/or multimedia solutions, then manage these projects from initial customer proposal through delivery, assuring the finished product is delivered in a timely manner through videography, production planning and execution and other creative functions.

raw_data.title: Video Editor**
raw_data.description: Select the most effective shot of each scene and combine them in sequence to form a logical and smoothly running story while keeping Director and Producer’s “vision” intact.

raw_data.title: Photographer**

raw_data.title: Media Manager

raw_data.description: The Media Planner/Buyer is to support to the entire media team; receiving new projects, adding them to multiple systems and assigning human resources to those projects. Negotiating media rates as well as in charge of all planning and media buying.

raw_data.title: Creative Director
raw_data.description: The Creative Director's primary responsibilities include planning, organizing and delegating work assignments on art projects, mentoring, developing and fostering a team environment, regulating the completion of assignments, and assuring proper execution on all projects.  Must be able to manage multiple concurrent analysis and development tasks in projects, Serve as point of contact with the Contracting Officer's Representative or Task Monitor, Formulate and enforce work standards, develop schedules, Review work discrepancies and communicate policies, purposes and goals of the organization.
